commText: de Kock and Rahul are at the crease. de Kock is on strike. Umesh Yadav will open the attack
Umesh Yadav to de Kock, no run, starts off with a length delivery around middle and leg, curves back in as de Kock knocks it down the pitch

Umesh Yadav to de Kock, SIX, de Kock gets off the mark with a maximum! Short of a length around middle and leg, de Kock stays put and pulls it over deep backward square leg for a towering six. That went high up in the night sky
Umesh Yadav to de Kock, no run, back of a length around middle and leg, de Kock clips it towards the on-side
Umesh Yadav to de Kock, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Umesh Yadav to de Kock, out Caught by Noor Ahmad!! Umesh Yadav has the last laugh! A length delivery around off, slides along the deck and de Kock gets a top edge as he looks to whip this across the line. Noor at third man settles under the skier and completes a safe catch as GT have struck in the first over. No de Kock special tonight as he walks back after hitting the only six. de Kock c Noor Ahmad b Umesh Yadav 6(4) [6s-1]
Devdutt Padikkal, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Review taken by Umesh against DDP for an lbw!

Umesh Yadav to Padikkal, no run, the inside edge saves Padikkal! Was a back of a length delivery that skids along the deck and Padikkal gets an inside edge on the back pad. The third umpire wasn't interested in checking UltraEdge as he spotted the deflection, but as it wasn't shown on the screen, Gill questions the onfield umpire. He wanted UltraEdge to confirm the same, however, umpire Nitin Menon didn't feel the need to go for it. GT have lost a review in the first over of the match itself
Umesh Yadav to Padikkal, no run, a successful over for GT! Back of a length around off, Padikkal defends it into the off-side
Spencer Johnson, left-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Now KL Rahul reviews! The onfield call is OUT, but Rahul reckons there's an inside edge and challenges the call..

Spencer Johnson to Rahul, no run, success for LSG! That was a length delivery and Rahul got an inside edge on to the pads as he tried to defend it. Would had been a horrible start for Lucknow was there no bat involved

Spencer Johnson to Rahul, leg byes, FOUR, fires this one on leg, Rahul tries to glance it away, but the ball flicks the batter's pads, beats the keeper's dive down the leg-side and races away to the fence
Spencer Johnson to Rahul, 1 run, pitched up by the bowler on off, holds its line as Rahul goes for a drive and gets an outside edge to third man
Spencer Johnson to Padikkal, no run, back of a length around off, blocked from within the crease into the off-side
Spencer Johnson to Padikkal, no run, pitched up by the bowler outside off, this ball shapes away from the batter as Padikkal goes for a flashy drive and gets beaten on the outside edge

Spencer Johnson to Padikkal, 3 runs, elegant shot, but an excellent save by Gill! Was on a length around off and Padikkal lofted it with poise over wide mid-off. Gill chases it all the way till the boundary, puts in a dive and flicks the ball inside. Saves one..
Umesh Yadav to Padikkal, FOUR, short of a length on middle and leg, Padikkal pulls this through square leg and strikes his first boundary of the match
Umesh Yadav to Padikkal, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Umesh Yadav to Padikkal, out Caught by Shankar!! Edged and taken! Umesh inflicting early damage with the new ball. Was a back of a length delivery outside off, shaping away from the batter and Padikkal played away from his body. Chases it with lack of footwork and the outside edge flies to the lone slip fielder. Shankar stationed there takes a good low catch and Padikkal's string of low scores continues.. Padikkal c Shankar b Umesh Yadav 7(7) [4s-1]
Marcus Stoinis, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Umesh Yadav to Stoinis, no run, back of a length around off, Stoinis defends it into the off-side
Umesh Yadav to Stoinis, no run, tad fuller on middle and leg, Stoinis knocks it firmly to mid-on
Umesh Yadav to Stoinis, no run, on a length around middle and leg, Stoinis looks to swing it across the line, gets an inside edge past the leg stump
Padikkal vs Umesh Yadav in the IPL Runs: 4 Balls: 8 Dismissals: 2
Umesh Yadav to Stoinis, no run, short of a length outside off, shaping away from the batter, Stoinis throws his hands at this widish delivery, connects thin air
Spencer Johnson to Rahul, FOUR, nicely timed drive. This was pitched up by the bowler and Rahul creams it through mid-off as he manages to beat the fielder's dive

Spencer Johnson to Rahul, FOUR, back-to-back boundaries. Width on offer, slightly fuller and Rahul has carved it over backward point. No one in the deep and that's four more. Rahul trying to be aggressive despite the loss of two early wickets
Spencer Johnson to Rahul, no run, 138.7kph, on a length around off, Rahul stays in the crease and knocks it towards point
Padikkal in IPL 2024 0(3) vs RR 9(6) vs PBKS 6(11) vs RCB 7(7) vs GT
Spencer Johnson to Rahul, no run, 143.2kph, back of a length outside off, keeps straight as Rahul shoulders arms
Spencer Johnson to Rahul, 1 run, back of a length around off, Rahul steers it towards the fielder at point for a single

Spencer Johnson to Stoinis, FOUR, creamed past the man at mid-off! This was pitched on a length and Stoinis plays it on the rise, times and places it neatly as the ball races away to the long-off boundary. Stoinis finally gets off the mark
Umesh to continue bowling, his third over of the powerplay..
Umesh Yadav to Rahul, 1 run, 142.5kph, pitched up by the pacer on off, Rahul drives it to mid-off and takes a single
Umesh Yadav to Stoinis, no run, short of a length around off, Stoinis taps it into the off-side

Umesh Yadav to Stoinis, 5 runs, oh no! There was chance of a run-out, but this ends up as 4 overthrows. Stoinis had nudged it towards cover and the fielder stationed there had a chance to nail a direct-hit at the bowler's end. The fielder backing fails to stop the ball and those are some bonus runs for Stoinis and Lucknow
Umesh Yadav to Rahul, 1 run, on a length around middle and leg, Rahul nudges it to mid-on with soft hands and scampers across

Umesh Yadav to Stoinis, FOUR, runs coming thick and fast. Drifting on the pads and Stoinis times his flick through mid-wicket. There were two fielders chasing it, but the placement and timing were just too good
Umesh Yadav to Stoinis, 1 run, 12 runs from that over. After a shaky start, LSG's innings getting back on track slowly. Short of a length on off and Stoinis steers it through backward point for one

Over Summary (1-5): -- Eventful 1st over: 6, QdK falls to Umesh, GT lose a review -- KL Rahul successfully challenges an lbw call -- Another failure for Padikkal as he nicks off for 7 -- Johnson concedes 3 boundaries off his 2nd over -- 12 runs off Umesh's 3rd over
A slip in place for Stoinis
Rashid Khan, right-arm leg break, comes into the attack
Rashid Khan to Stoinis, 1 run, Rashid Khan starts off with a googly as Stoinis nudges it into the on-side for one
Rashid Khan to Rahul, no run, appeal for an lbw, turned down. Was on the shorter side and on leg, Rahul tried to drag it through the leg-side, but got hit on the pads. Would have missed leg mostly
Rashid Khan to Rahul, 1 run, touch short on middle and leg, Rahul nudges it towards mid-wicket for a single
Rashid Khan to Stoinis, 1 run, quicker through the air as Stoinis works it towards mid-wicket for one more
Rashid Khan to Rahul, 1 run, too many googlies by Rashid Khan in this one. This being one of them. Rahul picks it and clips it to mid-on for a single
Rashid Khan to Stoinis, no run, flatter through the air on off, Stoinis guides it back to Rashid
Mohit Sharma, right-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Mohit Sharma to Rahul, no run, back of a length on off, Rahul knocks it in front of cover
Mohit Sharma to Rahul, 1 run, 136.9kph, short of a length around off, Rahul steers it to square third man

Mohit Sharma to Stoinis, FOUR, 50 up for LSG! Back of a length outside off, Stoinis looks to punch this through the off-side, ends up getting an outside edge through the vacant slip cordon and runs away to the fence. The fielder in the deep tried his best, but couldn't get there
Mohit Sharma to Stoinis, 1 run, tad fuller on off, Stoinis drives it to mid-off where Gill stops it with a dive, keeps them down to a single
Mohit Sharma to Rahul, 1 run, 136kph, back of a length on middle and leg, Rahul knocks it with soft hands to long-on, just a single
Mohit Sharma to Stoinis, no run, 135.5kph, short of a length outside off, Stoinis chops it towards backward point
A slip in place for Rahul..
Noor Ahmad, comes into the attack
Noor Ahmad to Rahul, FOUR, Rahul welcomes Noor Ahmad with a boundary. This was short outside off, kept a touch low as Rahul plays a late cut, beats the fielder at backward point and finds the fence
Noor Ahmad to Rahul, 2 runs, similar to the previous ball. This was on the shorter side and Rahul cuts it through backward point, the fielder sprinting across in the deep stops it this time around
Noor Ahmad to Rahul, 1 run, tad short on off, punched down the ground to long-off for one
Noor Ahmad to Stoinis, 1 run, pitched up by the spinner, slower through the air as Stoinis push-drives it to long-off for one
Noor Ahmad to Rahul, 1 run, tossed up delivery on middle and leg, Rahul sweeps it through square leg for a single
Noor Ahmad to Stoinis, no run, cut to backward point as it's a short one by Noor Ahmad
Rashid Khan [1.0-0-4-0] is back into the attack
Rashid Khan to Rahul, 1 run, played through mid-wicket for a single
Rashid Khan to Stoinis, 2 runs, tossed up delivery on middle and leg, Stoinis heaves it over square leg for a couple of runs, good stop in the deep by the fielder
Rashid Khan to Stoinis, 1 run, floated on off, Stoinis drives it to wide long-off for a single
Rashid Khan to Rahul, 1 run, 50-run stand up. That short on middle and leg, worked through the leg-side by Rahul for a single
Rashid Khan to Stoinis, 1 run, tad short on middle and leg, Stoinis nudges it to short fine leg for a single
Rashid Khan to Rahul, 1 run, a lot fuller on middle and leg, Rahul drives this along the carpet to long-on for one

Strategic timeout! A solid partnership building between Stoinis and Rahul after that early hiccup. de Kock couldn't contribute much today, and Padikkal failed again. Stoinis and Rahul have played well since then and got the innings back on track. Let's see if they continue to build on or the GT bowlers strike back..
Noor Ahmad to Rahul, 1 run, tad short outside off, Rahul cuts it through the off-side for a single
Noor Ahmad to Stoinis, no run, tad fuller on off, Stoinis knocks it into the off-side
Noor Ahmad to Stoinis, 2 runs, drifting on the pads, Stoinis works it through the on-side with soft hands for a couple of runs
Noor Ahmad to Stoinis, no run, tad short outside off, Stoinis chops it to the fielder at point
Noor Ahmad to Stoinis, 1 run, on the shorter side, slapped to long-off by Stoinis for a single
Noor Ahmad to Rahul, no run, floated on middle and leg, Rahul nudges it back to the bowler
Over Summary (6-10) - 31/0: -- Rashid starts with a tight over -- Rahul welcomes Noor with a boundary -- Fifty partnership in 38 balls between Rahul & Stoinis -- Ne freebies on offer from GT
Mohit Sharma [1.0-0-7-0] is back into the attack
Mohit Sharma to Stoinis, 1 run, short of a length on middle and leg, dragged through mid-wicket for one
Mohit Sharma to Rahul, 1 run, on the shorter side, sliced to square third man for one
Mohit Sharma to Stoinis, FOUR, short and punished! Stoinis swivels and pulls this through mid-wicket for a rollicking boundary. Slowly getting into his groove
Mohit Sharma to Stoinis, 2 runs, on a length around middle and leg, Stoinis clipped to long-on for a brace
Mohit Sharma to Stoinis, 1 run, tad short on off, Stoinis punches it in front of cover
Mohit Sharma to Rahul, 1 run, back of a length on off, Rahul steers it to point for a single
Noor Ahmad to Rahul, 1 run, tossed up delivery on leg, Rahul goes for a sweep, gets an inside edge on to the pads
Noor Ahmad to Stoinis, 1 run, loopy delivery on off, Stoinis drives it uppishly through cover for a single
Noor Ahmad to Rahul, 1 run, swept through mid-wicket by Rahul for a single

Noor Ahmad to Stoinis, no run, stumping opportunity missed. Stoinis had got an underedge towards the keeper as he tried to cut this, and he was outside the crease for a moment. Had the keeper managed to gather the ball quickly and dislodge the bails, this would have been interesting. Probably a stumping chance
Noor Ahmad to Stoinis, no run, slaps the short ball back to the bowler does Stoinis
Noor Ahmad to Stoinis, 1 run, clipped through mid-wicket by Stoinis for a single
Darshan Nalkande, right-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Darshan Nalkande to Stoinis, 1 run, short of a length on off, Stoinis punches it to long-off for a single
Darshan Nalkande to Rahul, 1 run, slower back of a length delivery on off, Rahul cuts it through point for a single
Darshan Nalkande to Stoinis, 1 run, chips the length delivery over cover-point for one
Darshan Nalkande to Rahul, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Darshan Nalkande to Rahul, out Caught by Rahul Tewatia!! "Power failure," quips Ian Bishop on air as soon as Rahul mistimes this. Was pitched up by the pacer and Rahul tried to go after him. Takes the aerial route and launches this towards long-on, but due to lack of timing and power behind the shot, ends up getting caught at long-on. Tewatia the fielder who takes the skier as the LSG captain walks back after playing a scratchy knock. Did a decent job of rebuilding the innings though. Rahul c Rahul Tewatia b Darshan Nalkande 33(31) [4s-3]
Nicholas Pooran, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Darshan Nalkande to Pooran, 1 run, pitched up by the bowler on off, Pooran drives it to wide mid-off for a single
Darshan Nalkande to Stoinis, 1 run, full and straight on middle and leg, Stoinis drives this along the carpet to long-on, just a single
Noor Ahmad to Stoinis, 1 run, tossed up full on the stumps, Stoinis gets forward to drive to long-on
A short-leg under the lid and a slip in. What will Pooran do?
Noor Ahmad to Pooran, 1 run, the googly and tossed up on off, flicked to the vacant mid-wicket area

Noor Ahmad to Stoinis, 1 run, dropped by Rashid Khan from long-off. Tossed up googly on middle and leg, Stoinis gets forward to loft, thick leading-edge and Rashid ran in a long way and slid, but drops it, Gill pats him on the back for that effort, how costly will that be?
Noor Ahmad to Pooran, 1 run, tossed up full outside off, square-driven to sweeper cover
Noor Ahmad to Stoinis, no run, flat good length googly on off, punched to extra-cover
Noor Ahmad to Stoinis, 1 run, short and wide outside off, cut to sweeper cover
Darshan Nalkande to Stoinis, SIX, 50 for Stoinis. He will now get a move on. A slower ball on a length outside off, Stoinis gets forward and swipes that hard and flat over long-on
Darshan Nalkande to Stoinis, 1 run, back of a length outside off, Stoinis drags the pull to deep square leg
Darshan Nalkande to Pooran, 1 run, fullish on off, driven on the rise to extra-cover
Darshan Nalkande to Stoinis, SIX, second six of the over. Full and angling into off-stump, Stoinis holds his shape and gets forward to loft over wide long-on, clean hit
Darshan Nalkande to Stoinis, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Darshan Nalkande to Stoinis, out Caught by Sharath BR!! Darshan Nalkande comes back well. Full on middle, Stoinis gets forward to loft and it's a thick top-edge that goes miles, Sharath BR does well to hold his composure and take it. Big wicket for Stoinis was looking to turn it on. Nalkande is pumped. Stoinis c Sharath BR b Darshan Nalkande 58(43) [4s-4 6s-2]
Ayush Badoni, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Darshan Nalkande to Ayush Badoni, 2 runs, back of a length and skiddy just outside off, Ayush Badoni mistimes the pull, in front of deep mid-wicket and comes back for two

Over Summary (11-15) - 40/2: -- Reprieve for Stoinis as Sharath fluffs a half-chance -- Nalkande breaks the 73-run stand as Rahul holes out to long-on -- Noor deceives Stoinis but Rashid drops him after covering the distance -- Noor Ahmad finishes with 4-0-22-0 -- 40-ball half-ton for Stoinis -- After conceding two sixes, Nalkande removes Stoinis
Timeout! Just when Stoinis was looking to up a gear, he fell but still Pooran is there and he is key for LSG to get above 170.
Spencer Johnson [2.0-0-17-0] is back into the attack
Spencer Johnson to Pooran, 1 run, good length on the stumps, turned to the square leg region
Spencer Johnson to Ayush Badoni, FOUR, half-volley outside off, angling away from Ayush Badoni who gets forward and stylishly drives wide of cover, on a bent knee and all
Marcus Stoinis’ innings \nvs Pace: 43(23), SR: 186.95 \nvs Spin: 15(20), SR: 75
Spencer Johnson to Ayush Badoni, wide, short of length down leg, Ayush Badoni pulls and misses
Spencer Johnson to Ayush Badoni, 1 run, throat-hugging short ball at Ayush Badoni who miscues the pull and gets away as there is no square leg
Spencer Johnson to Pooran, no run, big shout for caught behind, not given. Another short delivery at Pooran who goes for the pull, misses, close to the glove but no touch. GT don't take the review
Spencer Johnson to Pooran, no run, another fiery short ball at Pooran, who pulls and misses, flies over the bat and the glove, Pooran wants to know what height the short ball is, it is fine
Spencer Johnson to Pooran, no run, good length and tight on off, Pooran pushes it back. Fine over that
Rashid Khan [2.0-0-11-0] is back into the attack
Rashid Khan to Ayush Badoni, 1 run, back of a length outside off, punched to long-on
Rashid Khan to Pooran, no run, tossed up full outside off, in the slot and Pooran gets forward to loft, misses
Rashid Khan to Pooran, 1 run, the full googly outside off, Pooran drives wide of extra-cover for one
Rashid Khan to Ayush Badoni, 1 run, flighted delivery full on the stumps, dragged sweep to deep backward square leg
Rashid Khan to Pooran, 1 run, tossed up full on leg-stump, Pooran wants to heave this out of the ground but just finds deep mid-wicket
Rashid Khan to Ayush Badoni, 1 run, back of a length outside off, punched down to long-on
Mohit Sharma [2.0-0-17-0] is back into the attack
Mohit Sharma to Ayush Badoni, 1 run, back of the hand slower ball outside off, dragged to deep mid-wicket
Mohit Sharma to Pooran, SIX, Pooran picks the back of the hand slower ball now, outside off, on a length, heaved over wide long-on
Mohit Sharma to Pooran, 1 run, low full-toss on the pads, flicked to deep mid-wicket
Mohit Sharma to Ayush Badoni, FOUR, another back of the hand slower ball outside off, Ayush Badoni pulls hard and gets it wide of long-on, handy boundary
Mohit Sharma to Ayush Badoni, FOUR, another off-pace back of the hand slower ball outside off, Ayush Badoni delays the cut and beats backward point to his left, great execution
Mohit Sharma to Ayush Badoni, 1 run, good yorker outside off, dug out to cover. 17 off the over
Rashid Khan to Ayush Badoni, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Rashid Khan to Ayush Badoni, out Caught by Umesh Yadav!! Straight to deep mid-wicket. The slogsweep was on but Ayush Badoni could not get it off the middle. Rashid Khan has his first. Ayush Badoni c Umesh Yadav b Rashid Khan 20(11) [4s-3]
Krunal Pandya, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Rashid Khan to Krunal Pandya, 1 run, a juicy low full-toss outside the leg-stump, Krunal Pandya swings it straight to the fielder at deep backward square leg, missed out there
Rashid Khan to Pooran, SIX, there goes Pooran, tossed up on leg-stump, bowled from 24 yards too, Pooran slogsweeps on one knee and sends this over deep square leg
Rashid Khan to Pooran, 2 runs, shortens the length and gets it outside off, Pooran drags the heave, wide of deep mid-wicket and comes back for two

Rashid Khan to Pooran, 2 runs, outstanding from Sai at long-on. Pooran gets forward and lofts straight down the ground, was always four, but Sai sprints and palms it back, was four all the way but two saved
Rashid Khan to Pooran, 1 run, shorter and good length, the orthodox leggie, on middle, Pooran punches to long-off and retains the strike with that run
Spencer Johnson [3.0-0-24-0] is back into the attack

Spencer Johnson to Pooran, no run, was the attempted yorker, is a low full-toss on the pads, Pooran inside-edges it on to the pad, dribbles to mid-wicket and Spencer Johnson gets across and cuts it off
Spencer Johnson to Pooran, SIX, short of length on the stumps, Pooran stands back and slugs it over deep square leg, went a long way up and sailed over

Spencer Johnson to Pooran, no run, what a comeback from Spencer Johnson. That is a searing yorker on the stumps, late tail too, Pooran digs it out and falls flat on the ground, rolls to short fine-leg, superb delivery
Spencer Johnson to Pooran, no run, short outside off, Pooran slashes and misses, was there for the shot but missed out
Spencer Johnson to Pooran, 1 run, low full-toss sliding into the pads, Pooran gets an inside-edge on to pad on the heave, this time takes the single to backward square leg
Spencer Johnson to Krunal Pandya, 1 run, dug in short outside off, Krunal Pandya mistimes the pull to deep mid-wicket. LSG end on 163

21:15 Local Time, 15:45 GMT, 21:15 IST: GT will be very happy that they have kept LSG to 163. At least 20 short on this wicket. de Kock went early as did Padikkal but KL and Stoinis added a stand of 73 but they ate up a lot of balls. Both were striking around the 120 range. Just when KL looked to up the rate, he fell. Stoinis looked dangerous but after a couple of sixes against Nalkande, got out in the same over. The acceleration at the end never came as Rashid and Spencer Johnson were superb. Pooran did managed a 22-ball 32 but he struggled as he swung and did not connect as he would have liked too. Remember that LSG have never beaten GT before, can they do it tonight? Back for the chase in 5 minutes...

Umesh Yadav: I have been bowling with the new ball since the start of the tournament, but happy that I got a couple of wickets today. Have been working in the nets, having a word with Ashish Nehra as well, so happy that I executed my plans today. If you are accurate in the powerplay, chances of getting wickets is high. Just had to hit the right areas. The wicket is a little spongy, think a little dew has also started to settle in. Think 163 is chaseable.

LSG innings progression Overs 1-3: 18/2 (RR: 6) Overs 4-11: 66/0 (RR: 8.25) Overs 12-17: 42/2 (RR: 7) Overs 18-20: 37/1 (RR: 12.33) - LSG is the only team to score at less than 10 RPO (9.55) in death overs (16-20) in IPL 2024.

Nicholas Pooran in IPL 2024 64*(41) vs RR 42(21) vs PBKS 40*(21) vs RCB 32*(22) vs GT - He has hit 15 sixes and 8 fours across four innings and has scored at a strike-rate of 169.52.
Welcome back. LSG have their impact player - M Siddharth in, Stoinis out.
